description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Development Practice Education Facilitator (Placement Expansion) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12-month, fixed term / secondment &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very excited to open applications for a brand new Band 6 practice education role within the AWP Nursing Careers and Professional Standards Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are warmly invited from dedicated, dynamic and proactive Registered Nurses with a passion for student learning, and an appetite for transforming the way we approach practice education. The posts are open to any nurse with an interest in student learning, and would be a fantastic development opportunity for Band 5 nurses wanting experience of Trust-wide working, or opportunities to broaden their professional portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is being offered as 12 month, fixed-term contract (perfect for a secondment), funded by Health Education England as part of a national campaign to develop and expand high quality placement experiences for student nurses and other clinical learners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will focus on helping teams to support more students in a safe, effective and meaningful way. This will involve helping to implement new models of mentorship (such as ‘Collaborative Learning in Practice’), and expanding placements into non-nursing settings both within and outside of AWP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time opportunity (Monday to Friday 9-5), although some flexibility is preferred in order to accommodate the needs of clinical teams and their learners. Ability to travel Trust-wide is also required, although (due to the current COVID-19 pandemic) the work will rely heavily on remote working and video-conferencing platforms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think these roles could be the way forward for you, please make contact with the AWP Nursing Careers and Professional Standards Team by emailing Emily.carnell@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emily Carnell, Pre Registration Co-ordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;emily.carnell@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0117 378 4664&lt;/p&gt;
